The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Aug. 13: Work on the 3 million-tonne Jindal steel plant in Salboni will begin around Puja. 

 An in-camera public hearing on the environmental impact of the project will be conducted by the Union environment ministry in Midnapore on Friday. Officials of the pollution control board will also attend it. Work on the plant will begin after the ministrys nod, said Biswadeep Gupta, the project head. 

 Calcutta: A gang led by a woman, Ashima Halder, robbed a jewellers house in Diamond Harbour on Monday. But the ring leader was chased down by neighbours and ornaments worth Rs 1 lakh were recovered. When the house at Ratneshwarpur, 60km from Calcutta, was raided, Ritika Mondals husband was in his store.

 Tamluk: CPM supporter Sheikh Rafikul was arrested in Nandigram on Sunday night. A revolver was found on him.




